SIMPLE: penetration
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Penetration
<hw>Pen"e*tra`tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>penetratio</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>p⟦eacute⟧n⟦eacute⟧tration</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or
process of penetrating, piercing, or entering; also, the act of mentally
penetrating into, or comprehending, anything difficult.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And to each in ward part,⟦br⟧
With gentle <qex>penetration</qex>, though unseen,⟦br⟧
Shoots invisible virtue even to the deep.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>penetration</qex> into the difficulties of algebra.</q>
<rj><qau>Watts.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Acuteness; insight; sharp discoverment; sagacity;
<as>as, a person of singular <ex>penetration</ex></as>.</def>
<rj><au>Walpole.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Discernment; sagacity; acuteness; sharpness;
discrimination. See <er>Discernment</er>, and
<er>Sagacity</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Penetrative</ent>⟦br⟧
